<text xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="transcription"><body><div type="leaf"><p><pb facs="#f007"/>
                    <metamark>8</metamark>
                </p>
                <p><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z000" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">
                    --</add> "Methinks I should tremble now, were his <lb/> wizard power of gliding
                    through all impediments <lb/> in search of me, to place him suddenly before <lb/>
                    my eyes" <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z001" function="new-para" place="inline">[</metamark>How profound, nay appalling, is <lb/> the moral
                    evolved by the "Earth's Holocaust"<add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z003">;</add> <lb/> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z004" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">when</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z004" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">where</add><metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z005" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z006" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">--</add> beginning
                    with the hollow follies and <lb/> affectation<add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z007" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">s</add> of the
                    world, -- <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z008" hand="#ESM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">all vanities and </add><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z002" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="no-caret">empty</add><add><del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z010" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">lame</del> theories</add> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z009" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">
                    &amp;</add> <lb/> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z011" hand="#HM" place="margin" rend="no-caret">forms,</add> are<add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z013" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">, </add><metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z012" function="caret" place="inline" rend="insertion-line">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z013" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">one
                    after another, &amp; by an admirably graduated, </add><metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z014" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret"/><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z013" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">growing
                    comprehensiveness</add>; thrown into the allegorical fire, till, <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z015" hand="#HM" place="margin" rend="no-caret">at
                    length,</add> <lb/> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z016" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">gradually</del> nothing is left but the all-<lb/>engendering
                    heart of man; which remaining <lb/> still unconsumed, the great conflagration
                    is <lb/> <ref target="note_594af968520b4e46ae42e7fc4ccbe229">naught</ref><note xml:id="note_594af968520b4e46ae42e7fc4ccbe229">LW has "nought".</note>. <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z017" function="para-break" place="inline" rend="bracket">[</metamark><del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z017" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">of</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z017" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">Of</add> a piece with this, is the <lb/>
                    "Intelligence Office"<add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z018" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">,</add> a wondrous symbolizing <lb/> of <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z019" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z020" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">the</add> secret workings in <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z021" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z022" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">mens' souls.</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z023" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">this world.</del> <restore>
                        <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z024" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">There</del>
                    </restore> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z025" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">There</del>
                    are <lb/> other sketches, still more charged with <lb/> ponderous import.<note>It
                    appears that HM initially had a comma, followed by an em-dash, before "The
                    Christmas Banquet," and then rubbed out the dash and comma to render a full stop
                    before adding the bracket to indicate a new paragraph.</note> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z026" function="new-para" place="inline" rend="bracket">[</metamark>"The Christmas Banquet"<add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z027" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">
                        <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z027" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">,--</del>
                    </add><del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z027" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten"/><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z027" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">&amp;</add> "The <lb/> Bosom <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z029" hand="#ESM" place="above" rend="no-caret">Serpent"</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z028" hand="#ESM" rend="multistroke">friend"</del>
                    would be <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z030" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z031" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">fine subjects</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z032" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">excellent
                    things</del> <lb/> for a curious and elaborate analysis, touching <lb/> the
                    conjectural parts of the mind that produced <lb/> them. For spite of all the <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z033" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z034" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">Indian-summer</add> sunlight <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z035" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">in</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z035" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">on</add> the <lb/> hither side of Hawthorne's soul, the
                    other side -- like <lb/> the dark half of the physical sphere -- is shrouded <lb/>
                    in a blackness, <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z040" hand="#ESM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">ten times</add> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z036" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z037" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">
                    black.</add> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z038" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="no-caret">
                        <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z038" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">dark</del>
                    </add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z039" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">darker</del> <note>ESM
                    left a blank space and added "ten times" before HM made further revisions to
                    "darker".</note> But this darkness <lb/> but gives more effect to the
                    evermoving dawn, <lb/> that forever <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z041" hand="#ESM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">advances</add> through it, and <add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z042" hand="#ESM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">
                    circumnavigates</add> <lb/> his world. Whether Hawthorne has simply availed <lb/>
                    himself of this mystical blackness as a means <lb/> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z043" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">for</del> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z044" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f007_z045" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">to</add> the wondrous effects he makes it to
                    produce <lb/> in his lights &amp; shades; or whether there really <lb/> lurks
                    in him, perhaps unknown to himself, <lb/> a touch of Puritanic gloom,-- this, I
                    cannot</p>
            </div>

